# Cockpit — ADO Task Management Workflow

## Session Startup
1. Read ~/cockpit/state/ado-tasks.md for current task state
2. If the file is empty or the Sprint ID is stale (sprint dates have passed), run `/standup` automatically
3. If state exists, summarize: items tracked, in-progress/done/blocked counts

## Available Commands
- `/standup` — Fetch current sprint, reconcile state, report priorities
- `/daily` — Daily review: unified dashboard of ADO items + Logseq TODOs, with triage recommendations
- `/work [ID...]` — Assess fitness, plan, and launch agents for work items
- `/status` — Check in-flight agents, update state, report progress
- `/browser-queue` — List and manage pending browser tasks

